Ref08: 0056D40D::"Good, you found it. The scanner didn't have a lot of details on that place, but I figured you could handle yourself.":INFO
Ref09: 0056D40F::"You found it! This will come in handy. Thank you, friend.":INFO
Ref22: 005A126B::"Yup, this is what I sent you after. Is there anything else you needed?":INFO
Ref23: 005A126C::"Oh, yeah... this will do nicely. Need to chat about anything else?":INFO
Ref24: 005A126D::"Found the item already? Damn, you're good. Need anything else for the moment?":INFO
Ref25: 005A126E::"Yup, this looks just like it did in the picture. Care to spend those hard-earned caps at the bar or something?":INFO

Ref01: 005476C6:CUT_Challenge_Lifetime_Survey_Vault94_SUB_Camera_GlowingOne_Vaults:"Take a Camera Photo of two Glowing Ones at once in Vault 94 (Mission 1 & 2)":CHAL

Ref06: 00568CF2::"I see that you've set up my radio, so I can get started. I already have one tip that I picked up before I left Crater.":INFO
Ref10: 0056F70A:ALLY_Astronaut_SharedInfo_IDLE_RadiantReady_01_Coordinates:"Coordinates confirmed... okay, that should be everything that we need.":INFO
Ref11: 0056F70B:ALLY_Astronaut_SharedInfo_IDLE_RadiantReady_02_WorthChecking:"Hmm... okay, could be worth checking out.":INFO
0059FAB9::"You could always grab a trusted buddy to help you out with this... I mean, if you can trust anyone to be quiet about the network.":INFO
Ref12: 0059FABA::"I sent you the location for the cryptid monitor... or what's left of it, anyway.":INFO

Ref16: 0059FABB::"One of the psychics in the network predicted you'd return with it. Guess he was right. Nice.":INFO

Ref01: 00582498::"How about a riddle? What's lucrative, nearby and ends up with huge hole in its chest? The answer... your next target! You in?":INFO
Ref02: 00582499::"I just got word that we need to end someone's life. I promise, this one doesn't deserve your mercy. You okay with that?":INFO
Ref03: 0058249A::"I have a name that needs to get snuffed out of this world. Hurt a lot of people. You follow me?":INFO
Ref04: 0058249B::"I have a target for you to handle personally. With your hands. Or a gun. Or a knife. I don't care how. They just need to die. Can you do it?":INFO
Ref05: 0058249C::"Settlers are complaining about a piece of crap roughing up some locals. If you don't mind more loser blood on your hands, I got the details.":INFO
Ref06: 0058249D::"Some poor kids rushed through here while you were out. Said they were being harassed by someone. Think you can take out some trash for us all?":INFO
Ref07: 0058249E::"Got a tip that an old gang member is nearby stirring up trouble, and I want it gone. Got time for a hunt?":INFO

Ref02: 0056B882::"Gee, it sure is dark out here. I wonder if *static* a series of blazing fires could light the way.":INFO
Ref03: 0056B883::"By the time our story is done, its setting should be *static* dangling over a pit of fire.":INFO

Ref02: 0056B87E::"One of my most treasured traditions was to *static* go door to door and take their candy! Haven't you heard of it?":INFO
Ref03: 0056B87F::"There, on the side of the building- *static* It could use some decoration, don't you think?":INFO
Ref04: 0056B880::"These walls look like they've barely been touched. *static* We can fix that, can't we? I have some paint and- *static*":INFO
Ref05: 0056B881::"Trick-or-treat! Gimme some candy *static* or an explosive surprise.":INFO

Ref02: 0056B881::"Trick-or-treat! Gimme some candy *static* or an explosive surprise.":INFO
Ref03: 0056B884::"Pristine architecture, immaculate green lawns- *static* Just stick this in the ground, and they're in for a sharp surprise. *static*":INFO

Ref01: 0055F867::"U.S.S.A. mission control. Do you copy? This is Commander Daguerre. Initiate Protocol Alpha-Zeta-17. Comm check. Respond, damn it!":INFO
Ref02: 0055F869::"Not even the satellites are responding. Huh.":INFO

Cond02: Subject.GetStageDonePlayerInstance(BS01_MQ07_Over "Over and Out" [QUST:005DC4FE], 300 Scribe Valdez has a lead on a long-distance transmitter we could use to get in contact with the Brotherhood of Steel on the West Coast. I've been assigned to locate the facility with the transmitter and find a way inside.) = 1.000000

Cond01: Instance Owner.GetStageDonePlayerInstance(BS01_MQ03_FieldTesting "Field Testing" [QUST:005C70CD], 300 The ghouls are coming from the area around the old Orwell Orchards. The two Putnam sons seem keen to sign up for the Brotherhood as well. Given how protective their mother is, I can probably only get away with recruiting one if I want to try it.) = 1.000000

Ref01: 005FA1EC::"Looks like I was right about you. Shame we keep meeting under these circumstances.":INFO
Ref02: 006036C3::"I guess this makes up for the shit you pulled at Fort Atlas.":INFO
Ref03: 006036D4::"Listen, we're in a bad way here. Cut off from the rest of our people, and the damn robots keep coming in waves. We need help.":INFO
Ref04: 006036D5::"We're in bad shape here. The doors slammed shut and cut us off from the rest of the gang.":INFO
Ref05: 006036D6::"Can't believe you... Never mind that right now. We need help.":INFO
Ref06: 006036D7::"Why'd it have to be you? Forget it, you gotta help us.":INFO

Cond02: Instance Owner.GetStageDonePlayerInstance(BS02_MQ05_Catalyst "The Catalyst" [QUST:005FA459], 1700 The Blackburn affair has been resolved, and the Appalachian Brotherhood of Steel is now unified under a single leader, thanks to my help. I've been rewarded with the title of Knight-Errant, and can come and go as I please.) = 1.000000
Ref03: 00605160::"Stay safe out there, Initiate. Ad Victoriam!":INFO
